-- 
Banks Setting Aside Billions for Public Borrowers, WSJ Reports

-- B y   T h e o   M u l l e n
-- 
2011-02-16T01:16:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-16/banks-setting-aside-billions-for-public-borrowers-wsj-reports.html
Banks are setting aside billions of
dollars for loans to cities, states, schools and other public
institions as an alternative to the  bond market , the Wall Street
Journal reported, citing bank officials it did not identify.    JPMorgan Chase & Co . and  Citigroup Inc . are among the banks
offering direct loans to municipal borrowers and others to both
refinance and develop new projects, the newspaper said.  A spokesman for Citigroup declined to comment, the Journal
said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Theo Mullen at 
 tmullen11@bloomberg.net  